  "prompt": "Did Charles Simonyi ask before his job interview at Microsoft for a non-disclosure agreement form regarding his paperwork on Word and Excel?",
  "response": "Charles Simonyi, who was instrumental in the development of Microsoft Word and Excel, did not ask for a non-disclosure agreement form regarding his paperwork on these applications before his job interview at Microsoft. Simonyi joined Microsoft in 1981, bringing with him experience from Xerox PARC where he worked on the Bravo word processor, which influenced the development of Microsoft Word. At the time, non-disclosure agreements were less common in the tech industry compared to today, and Simonyi's contributions were part of the collaborative and innovative culture at Microsoft.",
